        "content": "# 🔍 How to Use Distributed Tracing\n\n## Search Traces\nThe table above shows the **20 most recent traces** ingested by Tempo.\n\n### View Trace Details\n1. Click on any **Trace ID** to view the full trace waterfall\n2. See span details, duration, and service dependencies\n\n### Search with Explore\nFor advanced trace queries:\n1. Go to **Explore** → Select **Tempo** datasource\n2. Use TraceQL queries: `{resource.service.name=\"demo-rhinometric\"}`\n3. Filter by tags, duration, status, etc.\n\n### Send Test Traces\nGenerate sample traces with:\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:4318/v1/traces \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"resourceSpans\":[...]}'\n```\n\n---\n\n📚 **Learn More:** https://grafana.com/docs/tempo/latest/traceql/",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
